# FieldGroup and Field Components Usage Guide

This guide explains how to use the `FieldGroup` and `Field` components from `@voila.dev/ui/components/field-group` and `@voila.dev/ui/components/field`.

## Component Structure

The field components are split into two main groups:

- **FieldGroup**: Container components for organizing multiple fields into groups, sets, and sections
- **Field**: Individual form field components for labels, inputs, descriptions, and errors

## Importing Components

```tsx
import { Field } from "@voila.dev/ui/components/field";
import { FieldGroup } from "@voila.dev/ui/components/field-group";
```

## FieldGroup Components

### FieldGroup.Root

The main container for a group of fields. Use this as the outermost wrapper when you have multiple field sets or sections.

```tsx
<FieldGroup.Root>
	{/* Field sets and fields go here */}
</FieldGroup.Root>
```

### FieldGroup.Set

A semantic `<fieldset>` wrapper for grouping related fields together. Use this to create logical sections within a field group.

```tsx
<FieldGroup.Set>
	<FieldGroup.Legend>Section Title</FieldGroup.Legend>
	<FieldGroup.Description>Section description</FieldGroup.Description>
	{/* Fields go here */}
</FieldGroup.Set>
```

### FieldGroup.Legend

A `<legend>` element for fieldset titles. Supports two variants:

- `"legend"` (default): Larger text for main section titles
- `"label"`: Smaller text for subsection titles

```tsx
<FieldGroup.Legend>Address Information</FieldGroup.Legend>
<FieldGroup.Legend variant="label">Show these items on the desktop</FieldGroup.Legend>
```

### FieldGroup.Description

A description paragraph for field sets. Use this to provide context or instructions for a group of fields.

```tsx
<FieldGroup.Description>
	We need your address to deliver your order.
</FieldGroup.Description>
```

### FieldGroup.Separator

A visual separator between field sets. Can optionally include text content.

```tsx
<FieldGroup.Separator />
<FieldGroup.Separator>or</FieldGroup.Separator>
```

### FieldGroup.Group

A nested group container for organizing fields within a set. Useful for checkbox groups, radio groups, or any collection of related fields.

```tsx
<FieldGroup.Group className="gap-3">
	<Field.Root orientation="horizontal">
		{/* Field content */}
	</Field.Root>
</FieldGroup.Group>
```

## Field Components

### Field.Root

The main field container. Renders as a `<fieldset>` and supports orientation variants:

- `"vertical"` (default): Stack label and input vertically
- `"horizontal"`: Place label and input side by side
- `"responsive"`: Vertical on mobile, horizontal on larger screens

```tsx
<Field.Root>
	<Field.Label htmlFor="username">Username</Field.Label>
	<Input id="username" />
</Field.Root>

<Field.Root orientation="horizontal">
	<Checkbox id="option" />
	<Field.Label htmlFor="option">Option</Field.Label>
</Field.Root>
```

### Field.Label

A label component that works with form inputs. Automatically handles styling for different field orientations and states.

```tsx
<Field.Label htmlFor="username">Username</Field.Label>
<Field.Label htmlFor="option" className="font-normal">Option</Field.Label>
```

### Field.Description

A description paragraph for individual fields. Provides additional context or validation hints.

```tsx
<Field.Description>
	Must be at least 8 characters long.
</Field.Description>
```

### Field.Content

A content wrapper for fields with multiple text elements (label + description). Use this when you have both a label and description in a horizontal layout.

```tsx
<Field.Root orientation="horizontal">
	<Field.Content>
		<Field.Label htmlFor="2fa">Multi-factor authentication</Field.Label>
		<Field.Description>
			Enable multi-factor authentication for better security.
		</Field.Description>
	</Field.Content>
	<Switch id="2fa" />
</Field.Root>
```

### Field.Title

A title component for fields that need a more prominent heading than a label. Often used in choice cards or complex field layouts.

```tsx
<Field.Root orientation="horizontal">
	<Field.Content>
		<Field.Title>Kubernetes</Field.Title>
		<Field.Description>
			Run GPU workloads on a K8s configured cluster.
		</Field.Description>
	</Field.Content>
	<RadioGroup.Item value="kubernetes" />
</Field.Root>
```

### Field.Error

An error message component that can display validation errors. Accepts either `children` or an `errors` array.

```tsx
<Field.Error>This field is required</Field.Error>

<Field.Error errors={[{ message: "Invalid email format" }]} />

<Field.Error
	errors={[
		{ message: "Password too short" },
		{ message: "Must contain uppercase letter" },
	]}
/>
```

## Common Patterns

### Basic Form with Field Sets

```tsx
<FieldGroup.Root>
	<FieldGroup.Set>
		<FieldGroup.Legend>Personal Information</FieldGroup.Legend>
		<FieldGroup.Description>
			Please provide your personal details.
		</FieldGroup.Description>
		<FieldGroup.Group>
			<Field.Root>
				<Field.Label htmlFor="name">Name</Field.Label>
				<Input id="name" />
			</Field.Root>
			<Field.Root>
				<Field.Label htmlFor="email">Email</Field.Label>
				<Input id="email" type="email" />
				<Field.Description>
					We'll never share your email with anyone.
				</Field.Description>
			</Field.Root>
		</FieldGroup.Group>
	</FieldGroup.Set>
</FieldGroup.Root>
```

### Checkbox Group

```tsx
<FieldGroup.Root>
	<FieldGroup.Set>
		<FieldGroup.Legend variant="label">
			Show these items on the desktop
		</FieldGroup.Legend>
		<FieldGroup.Description>
			Select the items you want to show on the desktop.
		</FieldGroup.Description>
		<FieldGroup.Group className="gap-3">
			<Field.Root orientation="horizontal">
				<Checkbox id="hard-disks" />
				<Field.Label htmlFor="hard-disks" className="font-normal">
					Hard disks
				</Field.Label>
			</Field.Root>
			<Field.Root orientation="horizontal">
				<Checkbox id="external-disks" />
				<Field.Label htmlFor="external-disks" className="font-normal">
					External disks
				</Field.Label>
			</Field.Root>
		</FieldGroup.Group>
	</FieldGroup.Set>
	<FieldGroup.Separator />
	<Field.Root orientation="horizontal">
		<Checkbox id="sync" defaultChecked />
		<Field.Content>
			<Field.Label htmlFor="sync">
				Sync Desktop & Documents folders
			</Field.Label>
			<Field.Description>
				Your folders are being synced with iCloud Drive.
			</Field.Description>
		</Field.Content>
	</Field.Root>
</FieldGroup.Root>
```

### Horizontal Field with Switch

```tsx
<Field.Root orientation="horizontal">
	<Field.Content>
		<Field.Label htmlFor="notifications">
			Push notifications
		</Field.Label>
		<Field.Description>
			Receive push notifications on your device.
		</Field.Description>
	</Field.Content>
	<Switch id="notifications" />
</Field.Root>
```

### Field with Error State

```tsx
<Field.Root>
	<Field.Label htmlFor="password">Password</Field.Label>
	<Input id="password" type="password" data-invalid={hasError} />
	<Field.Description>
		Must be at least 8 characters long.
	</Field.Description>
	{hasError && (
		<Field.Error errors={validationErrors} />
	)}
</Field.Root>
```

### Choice Cards with Radio Group

```tsx
<FieldGroup.Root>
	<FieldGroup.Set>
		<Field.Label>Compute Environment</Field.Label>
		<Field.Description>
			Select the compute environment for your cluster.
		</Field.Description>
		<RadioGroup.Root defaultValue="kubernetes">
			<Field.Label htmlFor="kubernetes">
				<Field.Root orientation="horizontal">
					<Field.Content>
						<Field.Title>Kubernetes</Field.Title>
						<Field.Description>
							Run GPU workloads on a K8s configured cluster.
						</Field.Description>
					</Field.Content>
					<RadioGroup.Item value="kubernetes" id="kubernetes" />
				</Field.Root>
			</Field.Label>
		</RadioGroup.Root>
	</FieldGroup.Set>
</FieldGroup.Root>
```

## Component Hierarchy

```
FieldGroup.Root (outermost container)
├── FieldGroup.Set (fieldset wrapper)
│   ├── FieldGroup.Legend (section title)
│   ├── FieldGroup.Description (section description)
│   └── FieldGroup.Group (nested field container)
│       └── Field.Root (individual field)
│           ├── Field.Label
│           ├── Field.Description
│           ├── Field.Content (for horizontal layouts)
│           │   ├── Field.Label
│           │   ├── Field.Title (optional)
│           │   └── Field.Description
│           └── Field.Error (optional)
├── FieldGroup.Separator (between sets)
└── Field.Root (standalone field, not in a set)
```

## Key Principles

1. **Use FieldGroup.Root** as the outermost container when you have multiple field sets or sections
2. **Use FieldGroup.Set** to group related fields semantically with a legend
3. **Use FieldGroup.Group** for nested collections of fields (checkboxes, radios, etc.)
4. **Use Field.Root** for individual form fields
5. **Use Field.Content** when you have both label and description in horizontal layouts
6. **Use Field.Title** for prominent headings in choice cards or complex layouts
7. **Use Field.Error** to display validation errors, either as children or with an errors array

## Orientation Guidelines

- **Vertical** (default): Best for most form inputs, especially on mobile
- **Horizontal**: Good for checkboxes, radios, and switches where the label is next to the control
- **Responsive**: Use when you want vertical on mobile and horizontal on larger screens

## Styling Notes

- Field components automatically handle spacing, alignment, and responsive behavior
- Labels in horizontal fields automatically adjust width and alignment
- Descriptions adapt their text balance based on field orientation
- Error states are automatically styled with destructive colors
- Use `className` prop to override or extend default styles when needed
